B.aq6=new A.K("A radiculopathy is an injury to a spinal nerve root -- the thick bundle of motor and sensory fibers that exits the spinal cord through a bony opening called the neural foramen. The most common cause in younger patients is a herniated disc; in older patients, it's degenerative foraminal stenosis from bone spurs (osteophytes).",null,B.iF,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null)
